{
  "stem": "9995.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I managed to get myself a job in a German kitchen, which means I had more soup.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I could eat raw potatoes, and turnips, and some carrots, so I had, at least, something in me that kept me alive.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Until one day I found that I had some lice, and then I know that I'm going to get another type of typhoid that was the-- what we called in German, [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "From itch, really, I was dying.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, at that time, we were already surrounded by the English, and the camp was supposed to go up, but they didn't manage.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, they were supposed to-- to kill us all.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But, and we had no water for several days.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was dying for water.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I couldn't eat.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, as a matter of fact, we had a so-called block [INAUDIBLE] that was a German Jewish woman, Mrs.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Frankel, who was arrested after the war.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't know what they did with her, but she was also a killer.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And whoever was dead, everybody else had to-- whoever was next to that person, to drag her out and put on the pile.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she saw that I was dying, and she dragged me out, and they put me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was laying on the pile of the dead bodies.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And next to me was my mother's friend, Mrs.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Korniwo.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She was a wife of a dentist, very elegant woman before the war, and she was about 40 years old.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she said to me a very thin voice, I can never forget this voice, she said to me, roll down from it, and go back and hide in the barrack, because I have a feeling that you will survive.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we knew that the English were close.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and then she died.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
